Bola Bamigbola, Osogbo Three men, Mohammed Sani, 20; Awal Ali, 19; and Waheed Akanmu, 29, have been arrested by policemen attached to the Operations Puff Adder, Zone XI Police Command, Osogbo, for allegedly receiving stolen items. Sani and Ali were arrested in their hideout in the Sabo area of Ibadan, Oyo State, while Akanmu was nabbed in Osogbo, Osun State. A statement by the Police Public Relations Officer for the zone, Adekunle Ajisebutu, on Thursday, said the suspects were arrested for fraternising with notorious armed robbery gangs and receiving stolen items from them. According to the statement, the suspects were arrested in Sabo areas of Ibadan and Osogbo following a petition by a victim, who was attacked in his house in Ore, Ondo State, by members of a notorious gang of armed robbers in May. “The armed hoodlums broke into the victim’s premises around 2.20am and dispossessed him of his valuables, including a Toyota Corolla car 2010 model, electronics such as plasma TV sets, phones, jewellery and other items at gunpoint,” Ajisebutu stated. The Assistant Inspector-General of Police in charge of Zone XI, Mr Adeleye Oyebade, called for more support in the task of ridding the zone of criminal elements. Copyright PUNCH.
